$ System.Data.CommandType (enum)

The `System.Data.CommandType` enum identfies the type of a → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/Common/DbCommand[`System.Data.Common.DbCommand`] instance. The enum has three values:
  • `Text` (which identifies an ordinary → development/databases/SQL/statement
  • `StoredProcedure`
  • `TableDirect`

{ Anonymous blocks in Oracle

  As I found out the hard way, in order to execute an → development/databases/Oracle/PL-SQL/block[(anonymous) block], the `CommandType` must not be set to `StoredProcedure`!

}

sa:
  Although similarly named, `CommandType` has nothing to do with → Microsoft/dot-net/namespaces-classes/System/Data/CommandType[`System.Data.CommandType`]
